    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Deseed your<strong> pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and dice</p><p>Add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> to a bowl with your <strong>ground</strong> <strong>smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>ground coriander</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chilli-lime-cod-with-charred-pepper-and-tomato-salsa/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> and <strong>diced</strong> <strong>pepper </strong>to the bowl and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Transfer the <strong>spiced potatoes & pepper </strong>to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!) and reserve the bowl along with any excess marinade</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 25 min or until the potatoes are crispy and the pepper is slightly charred</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chilli-lime-cod-with-charred-pepper-and-tomato-salsa/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate)<strong> half</strong> your <strong>garlic </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)</p><p>Chop your <strong>tomato[es]</strong> finely</p><p>Zest <strong>half</strong> your <strong>lime[s]</strong> (try to grate lightly with a micro-plane or sharp box grater and avoid grating the white pith, as this is very bitter)</p><p>Trim, then slice your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chilli-lime-cod-with-charred-pepper-and-tomato-salsa/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>tomato</strong> to the reserved bowl with your <strong>red wine vinegar</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>lime zest</strong> and <strong>half </strong>the <strong>sliced spring onion </strong>(reserve the rest for a garnish!) and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>tomato salsa</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chilli-lime-cod-with-charred-pepper-and-tomato-salsa/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely slice (don't chop!) the <strong>remaining garlic</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>zested</strong> <strong>lime[s]</strong> into 2 wedges per person</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chilli-lime-cod-with-charred-pepper-and-tomato-salsa/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes and pepper are almost ready, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a high heat</p><p>Pat your <strong>cod fillet[s]</strong> dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced garlic</strong>, your<strong> chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>butter </strong>and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chilli-lime-cod-with-charred-pepper-and-tomato-salsa/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>cod fillet[s]</strong> to the pan with the juice of <strong>half</strong> the <strong>lime wedges</strong></p><p>Cook for 4-5 min on each side or until cooked through \u2013 this is your <strong>chilli-lime cod</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chilli-lime-cod-with-charred-pepper-and-tomato-salsa/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>charred pepper & roast potatoes </strong>with the<strong> tomato salsa </strong>to the side, and top with the<strong> chilli-lime cod</strong></p><p>Drizzle over any pan sauce and garnish with a <strong>remaining lime wedge </strong>and <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>sliced spring onion</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
